One formal house and a backyard dwelling have been destroyed in the blaze from last night. CAPE TOWN Two minors have died in a fire incident in Mitchells Plain in Cape Town. One formal house and a backyard dwelling have been destroyed in the blaze from last night. Social services trauma councillors are providing therapy to the family. At least 30 dwellings have also been destroyed in a separate fire incident in Kensington earlier today. Fire and Rescue Service's spokesperson Theo Layne said, Approximately 120 people have been displaced and the cause of the fires is not known. 